-- Mitsubishi to Expand Water Membrane Business in Vietnam Accord
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2013-02-22T13:59:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-22/mitsubishi-to-expand-water-membrane-business-in-vietnam-accord.html
Mitsubishi Rayon Co., a Tokyo-based
unit of  Mitsubishi Chemical Holdings Corp. (4188) , reached an agreement
to expand its water-treatment membrane operations in  Vietnam .  The company, whose products include water-purification and
wastewater-treatment systems, chemicals, carbon fibers and
acrylics, said today in a statement that it entered into a pact
with the Ho Chi Minh-based engineering company Greentech
Environment to market hollow-fiber membranes for water-treatment
equipment installed in hospitals, hotels, factories and other
facilities. No terms were disclosed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in London at 
